Bitwise operators-

bitwise AND - &
bitwise OR - |
bitwise XOR (^)- (exclusive OR ) - same bit =0          1^1=0
                                diffenert bits = 1      0^1=1
bitwise left shift(<<) - shifting bit toward left       10<<2-> 1010<<2=101000=40
bitwise right shift(>>) - shifting bit toward right     10>>2-> 1010>>2=10=20





Operator Precendence-
                    priority

!,+,-               first (right to left)
*,/,%               second (left to right)
+,-                 third(left to right)
<,<=,>=,>           fourth(left to right)
==.!=               fifth(left to right)
&&                  sixth(left to right)
||                  seventh(left to right)
=                   last(right to left)





Scope - used to check variable forr accessibility and usability
        local scope - locally define (accessiblity inside the loops, conditions)
            ex-if{
                int x;
            }
            cout<<x; // error x is not accessible outside the if block
        global scope - globally define (accessible globally inside file)
            ex- int x; // global variable
                int main(){
                    cout<<x; // accessible globally
                }



Data types modifiers - used to modify the data type
                    signed - can store both positive and negative values
                    unsigned - can store only positive values
                    long - can store larger values than the regular data types
                    short - can store smaller values than the regular data types
                    long long - can store even larger values than long data type
                    long double - can store larger values than double data type